<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-size:medium;">Boss Mob</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;font-size:small;">Begining Fight</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- Open with Draughts so as to not gain aggro too quickly.<br>
- Do this until Mob is 90%.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;font-size:small;">Mid Fight</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- At 90% mana, click Mod rod.<br>
- Use Big nukes<br>
- At 90% mana again click Harvest 2<br>
- At 90% mana again click Harvest<br>
- Throw in concussions as needed<br>
- Somewhere in the mix refresh BoF<br>
- When mod rod refreshes, pop it.<br>
- When\if Harvest 2 refreshes, pop it.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;font-size:small;">End Fight</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- Typically I want 30% mana left when mob is at 9% health, if If it appears I'm not going to have this, I slow down.<br>
- If I feel I've built too much aggro prior to mob 9% health, I throw in numorous concussions when mob is at 12-15% to prepare for the fury that is about to be unleashed.<br>
- At mob 9% health, nuke hard, big spells, no concussion.<br>
- If I run OOM prior to the mob being dead, I watch my mana regen and how fast the mob is dropping, if I think I'm not going to get another big bang spell off before the mob is dead, I will throw a low mana draught at it.  If I think I can med up in time, I wait to throw out another big bang spell.<br>
